#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "Deploying raw images"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&productname; provides raw images that can be directly deployed to your "
"device storage&mdash;a memory card, USB flash drive, or a hard disk. The "
"options for which type of device you can deploy the image to depend on your "
"particular hardware&mdash;follow your vendor documentation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To initially configure the deployed image, you need to prepare the "
"configuration data as described in <xref linkend=\"pro-preparing-"
"configuration-device\"/> and you need to copy the configuration data to a "
"device (for example USB disk). The device needs to be connected to your host "
"running &slema; during its first boot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:31
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To prepare the setup, you need two separate devices. One for the raw disk "
"image, where &slema; runs, and another one that serves as a configuration "
"media."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:37
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preparing the raw disk image"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:39
#, no-c-format
msgid "Download the raw image and decompress it:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:42
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;xz -d <replaceable>DOWNLOADED_IMAGE.raw.xz</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:45
#, no-c-format
msgid "Copy the decompressed image to the device where &slema; will run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:48
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.user;dd if=<replaceable>DOWNLOADED_IMAGE.raw</replaceable> of=/dev/"
"sd<replaceable>X</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following procedure describes how to prepare the configuration device "
"(usually a USB flash disk)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:56
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preparing the configuration device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Format the disk to any file system supported by &slema;: Ext3, Ext4, etc.:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:61
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"&prompt.user;sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/sd<replaceable>Y</replaceable>\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set the device label to either <literal>ignition</literal> (when either "
"Ignition or Combustion is used) or <literal>combustion</literal> (when only "
"Combustion is used). For the Ext4 file system:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;sudo e2label /dev/sd<replaceable>Y</replaceable> ignition"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:72
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use any type of configuration storage media that your virtualization "
"system or your hardware supports&mdash;ISO image, a USB flash disk, etc."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:79
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mount the device:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:82
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"&prompt.user;sudo mount /dev/sdY /mnt\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:87
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create the directory structure as mentioned in <xref linkend=\"cha-images-"
"ignition\"/> or <xref linkend=\"cha-images-combustion\"/> , depending on the "
"configuration tool used:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:93
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"&prompt.user;sudo mkdir -p /mnt/ignition/\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:96
#, no-c-format
msgid "or:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:99
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"&prompt.user;sudo mkdir -p /mnt/combustion/\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Prior to booting for the first time, prepare all elements of the "
"configuration that will be used by <xref linkend=\"cha-images-ignition\" "
"xrefstyle=\"template:Ignition\"/> or <xref linkend=\"cha-images-combustion\" "
"xrefstyle=\"template:Combustion\"/> . The minimal configuration must provide "
"a password for &rootuser;, otherwise the system will not be accessible after "
"the first boot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the first boot, you need to register your &slem; instance by using the "
"command line tool <command>SUSEConnect</command> . For details, refer to "
"<xref linkend=\"sec-images-registration\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&slema; has available extension for live patching. To use this extension, "
"you need to add the extension to your subscription from the installed "
"system. For details, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-adding-extension\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:125
#, no-c-format
msgid "Registration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Registering the system is possible from the command line using "
"<command>SUSEConnect</command> . For information that goes beyond the scope "
"of this section, refer to the inline documentation with <command>SUSEConnect "
"--help</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:135
#, no-c-format
msgid "Product registration with SUSEConnect"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:137
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To register &productname; with &scc;, run <command>SUSEConnect</command> as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;SUSEConnect -r <replaceable>REGISTRATION_CODE</replaceable> -e "
"<replaceable>EMAIL_ADDRESS</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:142
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To register with a local registration server, additionally provide the URL "
"to the server:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;SUSEConnect -r <replaceable>REGISTRATION_CODE</replaceable> -e "
"<replaceable>EMAIL_ADDRESS</replaceable> \\\n"
"--url \"https://suse_register.&exampledomain;/\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:148
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replace <replaceable>REGISTRATION_CODE</replaceable> with the registration "
"code you received with your copy of &productname;. Replace "
"<replaceable>EMAIL_ADDRESS</replaceable> with the e-mail address associated "
"with the &suse; account you or your organization uses to manage "
"subscriptions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:157
#, no-c-format
msgid "&productname; is now registered."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:164
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding extension"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:166
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case you need to activate the live patching extension, list available "
"extensions by running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:171
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;transactional-update --quiet register -list-extensions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The output provides you with a command how to activate the live patching "
"extension:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"&prompt.root;transactional-update register -p sle-module-live-patching/15.3/"
"x86_64 \\\n"
"  -r <replaceable>registration code</replaceable>\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:183
#, no-c-format
msgid "To deactivate the extension, run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:187
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"&prompt.root;transactional-update register -d \\\n"
"  -p sle-module-live-patching/15.3/x86_64\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:193
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rebooting after activating/deactivating extensions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:194
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As the extension activation or deactivation is performed as a transactional-"
"update and thus creates a new snapshot, you need to restart your system to "
"boot to the new snapshot and apply the changes."
msgstr ""
